at_least_six_months_tt: "The following has been true for at least #v 6#! months (currently [ROOT.GetCountry.MakeScope.Var('restoration_timer_var').GetValue|v0]) #indent_newline:3 "

ep2_meiji.1.t: "Sonnō Jōi"
ep2_meiji.1.d: "The end of Sakoku has stirred a sense of powerlessness against foreign encroachment, undermining the authority of the [ROOT.GetCountry.GetRuler.GetLastName] clan. The enemies of the Shogunate have rallied around the slogan of #italic Sonnō Jōi#!: "Revere the Emperor, expel the barbarians"."
ep2_meiji.1.f: "On the second floor of a Kyōto inn, far from any windows, a dozen black-clad rōnin huddled around a table. Outside, rain poured down with a fury that drowned out the sounds of the street. Angry whispers passed between them—complaints, then denunciations, then a sworn oath and an interloper's death warrant.\n\nFar away, in a house overlooking Iso, a man in a green kimono watched a pillar of smoke ascend skywards. The hills cast long shadows over the constructions on the seashore. As the sun approached the horizon, the glow of the furnaces below grew more and more pronounced. Beyond them, reflected on the water, he could see the lights of ships. One day, he hoped, his cannon would banish them beyond the horizon."
ep2_meiji.1.a: "We must adapt to our new circumstances."

ep2_meiji.2.t: "The Shape of the Shogunate"
ep2_meiji.2.d: "The Shogunate reformers are split between two theories of governance. The theory of #italic Kōbu Gattai#! seeks to renew the legitimacy of the [GetLawType('law_bakufu').GetName] through fusion with the Imperial Court, whilst the theory of Public Deliberation seeks to establish a parliamentary system headed by the [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetLastName] clan."
ep2_meiji.2.f: "The host placed a tray of higashi upon the table, and poured a bowl of thin tea for each of his guests. Three men sat around the table, the host and first guest with their hair bound in chonmage, and the second short-haired. Steam wafted from the bowls in front of them.\n\nThe host directed his gaze to the short-haired man, and spoke.\n\n"I congratulate you upon your return, [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting]-#italic kun#!. I have found each of your letters more interesting than the last. Would you tell us more of your time with the barbarians?""
ep2_meiji.2.a: "The Bakufu must be renewed."
ep2_meiji.2.b: "Public deliberation is the enlightened way."

traditionalist_shogun_warning_tt: "@warning! A [GetIdeology('ideology_traditionalist').GetName] [ROOT.GetCountry.GetRuler.GetPrimaryRoleTitle] will be unwilling to pursue #b Parliamentary Government#!"
traditionalist_shogun_warning_present_tt: "[concept_ruler] does #b not#! have the [GetIdeology('ideology_traditionalist').GetName] [concept_ideology]"

ep2_meiji.3.t: "The Imperial Marriage"
ep2_meiji.3.d: "The Emperor has agreed to arrange a marriage between [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] and Princess [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_princess_scope').GetFullName]. The marriage is conditioned on the Shōgun's repudiation of the [SCOPE.sTreaty('relevant_treaty_scope').GetName], and return to an isolationist policy."
ep2_meiji.3.d2: "The Emperor has agreed to arrange a marriage between [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] and Princess [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_princess_scope').GetFirstName]. The marriage is conditioned on the Shōgun's expulsion of foreigners and return to an isolationist policy."
ep2_meiji.3.f: "The procession enveloped the entire Nakasendō. A train of thirty thousand laborers, retainers, and members of the Princess' household, guarded by a perimeter of soldiers of the Owari Domain, stretched from Iijima Town to Shiojiri Station. At the heart of the procession, the Princess rode atop a palanquin of gold and red silk. Alongside it rode samurai from a dozen domains—[SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_2_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')], [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_3_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_4_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')], [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_5_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_6_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')].\n\nWithin her palanquin, the Princess stared out of the thin gap between its curtains. Town after town passed by, shutters closed and silent. She would have the next thirty #italic ri#! to ponder her fate."
ep2_meiji.3.a: "For the good of the country."

has_broken_relevant_treaty_tt: "Has broken the [SCOPE.sTreaty('relevant_treaty_scope').GetName]"
ruler_does_not_have_imperial_marriage_tt: "[SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_marriage_ruler').GetFullName] has died or retired"

je_meiji_imperial_marriage: "The Imperial Marriage"
je_meiji_imperial_marriage_reason: "In [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_marriage_ruler').GetHerHis] pursuit of unifying the Imperial Court and Shogunate, Shōgun [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_marriage_ruler').GetFullName] has secured a political marriage with Imperial Princess [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_princess_scope').GetFirstName]. The Emperor's consent for the marriage is premised upon the expulsion of foreigners from the [GetGeographicRegion('geographic_region_home_islands').GetName], and a return to an isolationist policy.\n\nIf the Shōgun delivers upon [SCOPE.sCharacter('imperial_marriage_ruler').GetHerHis] vows, the marriage will contribute greatly to healing the rift between Japan's de jure and de facto rulers."

je_will_fail_tt: "The [concept_journal_entry] will #b fail#!"
je_has_timed_out_tt: "The [concept_journal_entry] has #b timed out#!"

ep2_meiji.4.t: "The [ROOT.GetCountry.GetCustom('get_sexagenary_cycle_term')] War"
ep2_meiji.4.d: "Alienated by the seizure of [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetHerHis] lands and titles, [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetPrimaryRoleTitle] [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] and [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetHerHis] loyal retainers have risen in revolt against the Imperial Court. [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetSheHe|U] seeks to reverse the restoration of Imperial power, and restore the Bakufu."
ep2_meiji.4.f: ""Your servant [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting], having earnestly considered the state of affairs since the ninth day of last month, finds that none of these events stem from the true intentions of the Imperial Court, but entirely from the conspiracies of the treacherous ministers of Lord [SCOPE.sCharacter('councilor_scope').GetLastNameNoFormatting]. This is known throughout the realm, particularly in Edo, Nagasaki, the provinces of Yashu and Sōshū, where disturbances have arisen.\n\nAs these are deeds detested by both heaven and man, we beseech Your Majesty to issue a decree for the surrender of the aforementioned treacherous ministers. Should this request not be granted, we shall have no choice but to proceed with their execution."" # Edited petition by Yoshinobu
ep2_meiji.4.a: "This is our wish: slay the traitor, and restore peace." # Emperor Meiji's plausibly fraudulent imperial decree of 1867
ep2_meiji.4.b: "The Emperor has come under the sway of robbers."

ep2_meiji.41.d: "Enraged by the efforts of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetLastName] clan to hold onto power, a coalition of restorationist domains have risen in revolt against [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName]. They seek to restore the political primacy of the Emperor, free from the influence of the Tokugawa."
ep2_meiji.41.f: "[SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] stood atop the castle walls, gazing down. Before him, row upon row of [SCOPE.sState('revolter_state').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_state')] soldiers filed out of the gates. Some were modernized, clad in the new uniforms, dark blue with conical helmets. Others retained their traditional clothing—reds, greens, blues. Those in the new uniforms were placed first in the column, and gained approving looks from the cluster of foreign observers who had placed themselves several metres to [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting]'s left. Behind them came the mounted samurai with their rifle-muskets, and after them the artillery.\n\nOn the outskirts of [SCOPE.sState('revolter_state').GetCityHubName] waited the staging ground, where they would meet the forces of their allied domains to march against the Shōgun's army. Far away, beyond that wall of swords and bayonets, the captive Emperor awaited."
ep2_meiji.41.a: "These fanatics must be repelled."
ep2_meiji.41.b: "Sonnō jōi!"

kinmon_civil_war_tt: "The [ROOT.GetCountry.GetName] will fall into a #r $concept_civil_war$#! between #b Shogunate#! and #b Imperial Court#!"

ep2_meiji.5.t: "Taisei Hōkan"
ep2_meiji.5.d: "Facing increasing pressure from the opponents of the [GetLawType('law_bakufu').GetName], [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] has petitioned the Emperor to return [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetHerHis] governing authority to the Imperial Court."
ep2_meiji.5.f: ""Unless power is reunited within the Imperial Court, the very foundations of our nation cannot be sustained. Therefore, at this juncture, we must reform the old ways, and return the administration to the Imperial Court.\n\nAfter exhausting the public counsel of the realm, and seeking Your Majesty's final judgment, I sincerely believe that if all hearts are united in service to the nation, we can protect our imperial country together and stand as equals alongside the nations of the world."\n\n—Tokugawa Yoshinobu, 1867"
ep2_meiji.5.a: "Naught but air beneath his feet."

ep2_meiji.51.t: "The Imperial Sanction"
ep2_meiji.51.d: "The Emperor has issued his response to [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName]'s petition to return governing authority to the Imperial Court. The Shōgun's petition has been accepted, and the political supremacy of the Emperor restored."
ep2_meiji.51.f: ""The Emperor of Japan announces to the sovereigns of all foreign countries and to their subjects that permission has been granted to the Shōgun [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting] to return the governing power in accordance with his own request. We shall henceforth exercise supreme authority in all the internal and external affairs of the country. Consequently, the title of Emperor must be substituted for that of Taikun, in which the treaties have been made. Officers are being appointed by us to the conduct of foreign affairs. It is desirable that the representatives of the treaty powers recognize this announcement.""
ep2_meiji.51.a: "A terrible thrill."

ep2_meiji.52.t: "The Imperial Sanction"
ep2_meiji.52.d: "The Emperor has issued his response to [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName]'s petition to return governing authority to the Imperial Court. The response states that the Shōgun retains the confidence of the Court, and that governing authority may remain with the Shogunate."
ep2_meiji.52.f: "[ROOT.GetCountry.GetCustom('japan_choshu_castle_name')] Castle echoed with the sound of boots. Messengers and retainers had been in and out all day, bearing increasingly detailed retellings of the last week's news. [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting] had personally received them, remaining resolutely silent through each meeting. His brow had grown heavier and heavier as he heard of the developments—the Shōgun's triumphal procession, the Aizu left guarding the Imperial Palace.\n\nOutside the front palace, the sun had set. From his stage, [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] looked to the twenty assembled retainers. "Chōshū Domain shall not submit," [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetSheHe] said. "Understand this well."\n\nHe rose, and exited the room."
ep2_meiji.52.a: "The branches embrace him."

ep2_meiji.6.t: "The Decree of Restoration"
ep2_meiji.6.d: "Opponents of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetLastName] clan within the Court have persuaded the Emperor to issue a decree formally restoring his own power. The decree abolishes the Shogunate, and establishes a government that excludes [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] from any official position."
ep2_meiji.6.f: ""[SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting] has requested that the administrative authority which had long been commissioned be restored, and now wishes to resign from the office of Shōgun. His proposal has been accepted. The country is threatened by incomparable dangers, with which, as it is well known, the late Emperor had seriously occupied himself. Accordingly, it has been decided by His Majesty's wise deliberation that the foundation for restoring imperial rule and reviving national dignity be laid.\n\nHenceforth, the offices of Sessho, Kanpaku and Shōgun shall be abolished, and the three offices of Chief Councillor, Councillor of State, and Councillor of the Palace shall be established. Everything shall be decided through the reasonable deliberation of the people, without any distinction between civil and military officers, between nobles and common people."" #- Modifier text of the Great Proclamation of the Restoration of Imperial Rule
ep2_meiji.6.a: "Alone in the dark."

ep2_meiji.7.t: "The Taikunate"
ep2_meiji.7.d: "With the Imperial Court lacking the practical expertise to govern, allies of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetLastName] clan within the Court have persuaded the Emperor to grant [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] the title of Taikun, placing [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetHerHim] at the head of the Imperial Office."
ep2_meiji.7.f: ""As the various Daimyō gradually assemble and gather, deliberation will take place. The spirit of the times is focused upon public deliberation—this phrase is widely discussed—and it has been unavoidable to go along with public opinion. Therefore, I earnestly request that, as far as possible, these discussions be brought to agreement, and that measures be taken so that the purpose of the assembly is properly established.\n\nShould discord arise in the course of deliberation, and conflict break out, even if it results in a victory for your house, it would be equivalent to brothers quarreling within the walls while foreign nations press upon us from outside."\n\n—Nishi Shūsuke, "Draft Agenda""
ep2_meiji.7.a: "On safe ground once more."

ep2_meiji.8.t: "Court and Shogunate"
ep2_meiji.8.d: "Through marriage into the Imperial Family and fulfillment of [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetHerHis] vows to the Emperor, [SCOPE.sCharacter('shogun_scope').GetFullName] has eased the tensions between Court and Shogunate. The Emperor may continue [SCOPE.sCharacter('emperor_scope').GetHerHis] secluded existence, assured that the Shōgun will ensure lasting peace."
ep2_meiji.8.f: "Even if stormy winds\nShould rage through the country,\nI shall wait for them\nTo return the sun in heaven\nTo its pristine radiance.\n\n—Emperor Kōmei"
ep2_meiji.8.a: "The storm has come to an end."

ep2_meiji.9.t: "First Among Equals"
ep2_meiji.9.d: "Through confidence and deft maneuver, [SCOPE.sCharacter('taikun_scope').GetFullName] has seen through both the restoration of the Emperor and the preservation of [SCOPE.sCharacter('taikun_scope').GetHerHis] clan. The [SCOPE.sCharacter('taikun_scope').GetLastName] Taikuns will reign as first among the peerage of a modern $JAP$."
ep2_meiji.9.f: "The Emperor no longer sat behind a screen. His ministers were arrayed along the table before him, with the Taikun to his left. Each wore a new court uniform, their sleeves and breasts decorated with intricate arrangements of gold leaf. Medals clicked and rustled as they adjusted themselves in the unfamiliar seats.\n\nThe Taikun had moderated the discussion for the past hour, with the Emperor not speaking a single word. He had been content to listen in, directing his attention to each speaker in turn. On the far side of the room, a former disciple of #italic sonnō jōi#! spoke of the necessity of a mission to America."
ep2_meiji.9.a: "The Shōgun falls, the Taikun rises."
ep2_meiji.9.b: "The Emperor is the Son of Heaven, and the Tokugawa his instruments."

