modifier_enraged_restorationists_debug: "#todo Enraged Restorationists#!"

ep2_meiji_pulse.1.t: "The Right to Strike"
ep2_meiji_pulse.1.d: "Whilst traveling in [SCOPE.sState('relevant_treaty_port_state').GetName], a [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] merchant was killed by the retinue of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetFullName] for refusing to dismount as he passed. The Daimyō of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] has asserted the legality of the killing under the right to strike any commoner who disrespects him."
ep2_meiji_pulse.1.f: "The foreigners broke the ranks of the musketeer squad, and shouts came from all around. Noticing the armed men surrounding him, the foreigner in the lead lashed his reins to the side, sending his horse into a rapid turn that very nearly knocked one of the musketeers off his own mount. [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] drew his sword, and his companions in the inner ring joined him.\n\n[SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] struck the first blow, opening a gash along the interloper's side. He shrieked, and lashed the reins once more. It was fruitless. The musketeer closest to him drew his own blade, and lashed out. An arc of red hung in the air like a cloud."
ep2_meiji_pulse.1.a: "The [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] wish for nothing more than to cause us trouble."

ep2_meiji_pulse.11.t: "The [SCOPE.sCharacter('richardson_scope').GetLastNameNoFormatting] Affair"
ep2_meiji_pulse.11.d: "Whilst conducting business in [SCOPE.sCountry('japan_scope').GetName], a [ROOT.GetCountry.GetAdjectiveNoFlag] merchant by the name of [SCOPE.sCharacter('richardson_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting] has been murdered by the local lord [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetFullName]. The lord has claimed [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHerselfHimself] justified under the law of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHerHis] land, and refused to pay any sort of compensation for [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHerHis] crime."
ep2_meiji_pulse.11.f: "#b Editorial#!\n\nUnder the present circumstances, we repeat that [ROOT.GetCountry.GetNameNoFormatting] has no alternative but to make ready for a great war, or to bid farewell to Japan. To abandon the foothold she has obtained there will not be thought of, and so we may look out for a conflict between the two empires. Many [SCOPE.sCulture('primary_culture_scope').GetCustom('getPluralDemonym')] dislike this idea, yet the [ROOT.GetCountry.GetCapital.GetCityHubName] [SCOPE.GetRootScope.GetCountry.GetCustom('generic_newspaper_type')] deems it not only inevitable, but justifiable, merely on the ground of the refusal of the Japanese to punish the assassins of [SCOPE.sCharacter('richardson_scope').GetLastNameNoFormatting]... (#italic cont. pg.02#!)" #largely copied from The Anglo-Japanese War, New York Times, 1863
ep2_meiji_pulse.11.a: "#italic Someone#! must pay. Raise the matter with the Tycoon."
ep2_meiji_pulse.11.b: "Do we truly wish to get further involved in the East?"

modifier_namamugi_incident_prestige_loss: "Tolerated Slain Merchant"

castle_yamaguchi: "Yamaguchi"
castle_hagi: "Hagi"

ep2_meiji_pulse.2.t: "The Bombardment of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHomeState.GetCustom('japan_domain_seat_name')]"
ep2_meiji_pulse.2.d: "In retaliation for the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Domain's refusal to pay an indemnity for the death of [SCOPE.sCharacter('richardson_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting], [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] naval vessels have engaged in a multi-day artillery duel with the coastal defenses of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHomeState.GetCustom('japan_domain_seat_name')]."
ep2_meiji_pulse.2.f: "The bay hung hazy with cannon fire, and [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetHomeState.GetCustom('japan_domain_seat_name')] was burning. Across the water, one of the foreign ships was firing rockets into the foundries in the North of the town. With each launch, a hellish red glow drowned out the feeble light of the setting sun.\n\nThe last operational cannon at [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting]'s battery roared—a long shot, in good conditions, and hopeless now. The ball impacted several lengths from the third vessel in the foreign column, sending a mighty gout of water into the air. [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] grabbed [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetHerHis] sponge, and rushed to attend to the gun. Somewhere behind the rear wall, the men wounded by the last salvo were still screaming. Somehow, despite the ringing in [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetHerHis] ears, [SCOPE.sCharacter('name_a_scope').GetSheHe] could still hear them."
ep2_meiji_pulse.2.a: "A harsh price for their recklessness."

