domain_seat_matsumae: "Matsumae"

ep2_meiji_pulse.3.t: "The Shimonoseki War"
ep2_meiji_pulse.3.d: "[SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetFullName], Daimyō of Chōshū Domain, has signaled [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetHerHis] compliance with the Emperor's order to expel foreigners. [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetSheHe|U] has ordered [SCOPE.sCharacter('choshu_daimyo_scope').GetHerHis] navy to fire upon all foreign vessels passing through the Shimonoseki Strait, spurring exchanges of fire with a [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] warship."
ep2_meiji_pulse.3.f: "Daylit thunder rolled over the gentle slope of Hinoyama, and Masatake's head turned to the sky. He was greeted by a puffy, white cloud.\n\n"Look!" cried Jiro. A hand entered his field of vision, pointing downwards. A ship at full steam was charging through the strait below, cannons blazing at something Masatake could not see. Splinters flew from her hull, and yet she continued. Above it all, another cloud was growing."
ep2_meiji_pulse.3.a: "The foreigners do what we cannot."
ep2_meiji_pulse.3.b: "Assist the Domain in reaching a settlement."
ep2_meiji_pulse.3.c: "Offer the Westerners a port in exchange for an accord."

treaty_name_shimonoseki_war_indemnity: "Shimonoseki War Indemnity"
modifier_defeated_westerners: "Defeated Western Expedition"
modifier_bombardment_of_domain: "Domain Seat Bombarded"

ep2_meiji_pulse.4.t: "The Burning of the [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] Legation"
ep2_meiji_pulse.4.d: "#italic Sonnō Jōi#! samurai of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Domain have staged an attack on the in-construction [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] legation building in [SCOPE.sState('edo_state').GetCityHubName]. What would have been the first Western-styled building in the city has been burned to the ground, with the perpetrators nowhere in sight."
ep2_meiji_pulse.4.f: "Two men, hooded and masked, settled in atop the hill overlooking what would have been the legation. An orange glow still rose from its now-blackened shell. With all more accessible fuel extinguished, the flames struggled to sustain themselves on the dense inner beams.\n\nAs the glow faded to nothing, the two men remained. One spoke, voice quiet, staring off at the pillar of smoke left behind.\n\n"Would it not be beautiful if its ashes were to fall on us like snow?""
ep2_meiji_pulse.4.a: "[SCOPE.sState('edo_state').GetCityHubName] has become ungovernable."
ep2_meiji_pulse.4.b: "Forbid the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] from bearing arms in the city."

shimonoseki_indemnity_tt: "[ROOT.GetCountry.GetName] will pay an indemnity of @money!#v 3M#! over #v 10 years#! to [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetName]"
shimonoseki_indemnity_port_tt: "The city of $HUB_NAME_STATE_KANSAI_port_japanese$ in [GetStateRegion('STATE_KANSAI').GetName] will be opened as a [SCOPE.sCountry('relevant_gp').GetAdjective] [concept_treaty_port]"

modifier_ungovernable_capital: "Admitted Ungovernability"

ep2_meiji_pulse.5.t: "A Bloody Revenge"
ep2_meiji_pulse.5.d: "The Chief Minister of the Shogunate, [SCOPE.sCharacter('tairo_scope').GetFullName], has been assassinated at the gate of Edo Castle by rōnin of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_2_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Domains. The manifesto left by the assassins expresses #italic Sonnō Jōi#! principles, condemning the Chief Minister's concessions to foreigners."
ep2_meiji_pulse.5.f: "Chuzaburo watched Gorokuro step in front of the procession, and one of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('tairo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] guards move to intercept him. Gorokuro gave him no more time to react. He drew his sword, and lunged. A great arc of blood flew from the [SCOPE.sCharacter('tairo_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] man's bisected face, and his companions surged forwards to avenge him.\n\nChuzaburo let his raincoat fall, and drew his pistol. He took aim at the exposed side of the palanquin, and pulled the trigger. The roar of a gunshot interrupted the sound of clashing blades and shouts, and then another. One of the guards wheeled to face him, and Jizaemon, the rōnin from [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_2_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')], swung his sword down towards his torso. Past the clashing duo, Chuzaburo could see a river of red trickling through the palanquin's doors, onto the snowy street. He drew his wakizashi, and ran towards it."
ep2_meiji_pulse.5.a: "The samurai cross blades once more."

modifier_tairo_assassinated: "Tairō Assassinated"

ep2_meiji_pulse.6.t: "The Ikedaya Incident"
ep2_meiji_pulse.6.d: "Guided by information gained by the torture of a militant of the [SCOPE.sPoliticalMovement('restorationist_movement_scope').GetName], the [GetLawType('law_shinsengumi').GetName] have launched a raid against a gathering of alleged conspirators at [SCOPE.sState('kyoto_state').GetName]'s Ikedaya Inn. The raid has transformed into a fierce sword battle in and around the inn."
ep2_meiji_pulse.6.f: "Otaka braced himself against the railing as the Shinsengumi burst through the door. He could see the bloodstains on the sleeves of their pale blue #italic haori#!—black-on-white in the dim lamplight. He raised his sword into a guard position.\n\nTwo of them detached from the rest, charging up the stairwell he guarded, two abreast. He struck out with his blade, felt it be parried, compensated. Sparks flew from the impact. The second man was striking out. He took a step back, twisted his wrist to-\n\nThere was a flash of fire-lit steel, and then something cold in his chest."
ep2_meiji_pulse.6.a: "Reward the Shinsengumi for their initiative."
ep2_meiji_pulse.6.b: "This brutality only invites retaliation."

modifier_shinsengumi_meddling: "Rampant Shinsengumi"
modifier_shinsengumi_crackdown: "Shinsengumi Crackdown"
modifier_refrained_from_crackdowns: "Restrained Shinsengumi"

sufficient_pressure_from_sonno_joi_tt: "[concept_activism] of the [SelectLocalization(SCOPE.sPoliticalMovement('meiji_movement_scope').IsValid, SCOPE.sPoliticalMovement('meiji_movement_scope').GetName, 'movement_meiji_restorationist_name')] is above @activism_red! $RADICALISM_PROTESTING$ (#v [GetDefine('NPolitics', 'RADICALISM_PROTESTING_THRESHOLD')|%0]#!)"

ep2_meiji_pulse.7.t: "The Forbidden Gate"
ep2_meiji_pulse.7.d: "Soldiers of the [SCOPE.sPoliticalMovement('restorationist_movement_scope').GetName]-aligned [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Domain have attempted to storm the Imperial Palace in [SCOPE.sState('kyoto_state').GetName], and restore the Emperor by force. They are opposed by soldiers of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_2_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and Aizu domains."
ep2_meiji_pulse.7.f: "The Hamaguri Gate was choked with gunsmoke. All around them, Kyōto was catching light.\n\nThe Aizu soldiers were concentrated along the wall, sending out volleys of musket-fire that scattered off the road and the chassis of the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] cannons. Every few seconds, one of the balls would strike flesh, spurring cries that briefly cut above the crackle of gunfire. Kōzō huddled against a wheel of a cannon, struggling to unjam his musket. A bare #italic ken#! away, the leader of his squad lay face down, legless, armless. Somehow, he was still writhing."
ep2_meiji_pulse.7.a: "The [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_2_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] and Aizu succeed in repelling the attackers."
ep2_meiji_pulse.7.b: "The Imperial Palace falls under [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] control."

coup_resistance_below_daimyo_coup_strength_tt: "The [ROOT.GetCountry.GetName]'s [concept_coup_resistance] ([SCOPE.ScriptValue('country_coup_resistance')|v2]) is below [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetFullName]'s [concept_coup_strength] ([SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').MakeScope.Var('monthly_cached_commander_coup_strength').GetValue|v2])"

ep2_meiji_pulse.8.t: "The [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Expedition"
ep2_meiji_pulse.8.d: "As retaliation for the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] assault on the Imperial Palace, the Shōgun has ordered a punitive expedition to expel the #italic Sonnō Jōi#! faction from the Domain. Advisors sympathetic to the [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] have offered a plan to secure peace in return for the seppuku of the guilty parties."
ep2_meiji_pulse.8.f: "[SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetFullNameNoFormatting], Daimyō of [SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')], stood on the castle's balcony, gazing into the distance. Far away, the sky was tainted by streams of smoke—the campfires of the approaching army.\n\n"The Shōgun demands the seppuku of the three senior retainers," said the retainer. "The beheading of the four staff officers. The exile of the five ministers."\n\n[SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetFirstNameNoFormatting] looked to the campfires. There were hundreds, at least. The once-blue horizon had become something sick. At last, he spoke.\n\n"...[SCOPE.sCharacter('daimyo_1_scope').GetCustom('japan_domain_by_character')] Domain will submit.""
ep2_meiji_pulse.8.a: "If they can be defeated without fighting, so be it."
ep2_meiji_pulse.8.b: "The Domain must be cleansed from top to bottom."

modifier_daimyo_house_arrest: "Confined Daimyō"
modifier_daimyo_executed: "Daimyō Dispossessed"

ep2_meiji_pulse.9.t: "The Order to Expel Barbarians"
ep2_meiji_pulse.9.d: "Angered by the treaties forced upon [ROOT.GetCountry.GetName] by the Western powers, the Emperor has bypassed the Shōgun and issued an edict to expel foreigners from [ROOT.GetCountry.GetAdjectiveNoFormatting] soil. Militants of the [SCOPE.sPoliticalMovement('restorationist_movement_scope').GetName] have rallied to the Emperor's cause."
ep2_meiji_pulse.9.f: "The retainer stood abreast one of the cannons, looking out towards the strait. At this hour, the vessels steaming through were silhouetted by the setting sun. Off to the side, the lower samurai of Chōshū Domain busied themselves with ramrods and bags of black powder.\n\nAs looked up at the shape of Hinoyama and the town of Shimonoseki below, passage from the Edict came to mind. "Even if the land were to be reduced to ashes," it had stated, "we shall not permit the opening of ports for trade."\n\nWas it justified? Would he permit for its gentle, green slope to be scorched black, for its fields of flowers to be burned, for his home to be leveled? Yes, he thought. Without hesitation."
ep2_meiji_pulse.9.a: "The Shōgun must travel to Kyōto to discuss this."
ep2_meiji_pulse.9.b: "This order is fraudulent—have it suppressed."

