shogunate_strategy_title_decide_loc: "Decide Reform Strategy"
shogunate_strategy_title_revise_loc: "Revise Reform Strategy"
shogunate_strategy_title_decide_desc_loc: "For the power of the Tokugawa to survive, the Shogunate must reform. Such a reform may proceed in one of two directions—the Shōgun may seek to renew the legitimacy of the Bakufu through unification with the Imperial Court, or he may pursue restoring the Emperor in a controlled fashion, to place himself at the head of a parliamentary government."
shogunate_strategy_title_revise_desc_loc: "The Shōgun's present strategy for reform has proven not necessarily advantageous. Though changing approach will incur a cost, it is best not to adhere to a failed course."

je_meiji_restoration_proclaim_imperial_restoration: "Petition for Imperial Restoration"
je_meiji_restoration_proclaim_imperial_restoration_desc: "[ROOT.GetCountry.GetCustom('get_imperial_restoration_button_loc')]"

imperial_restoration_unavailable_loc: "The Emperor remains the sovereign of Japan. Without the Imperial sanction, the Shōgun is merely the most powerful Daimyō amongst hundreds. The Shogunate's survival—or its fall—will depend upon the will of the Imperial Court."
imperial_restoration_kobu_gattai_loc: "For the crisis to end, there must be union between Shogunate and Court. The Daimyō must be convinced that the orders of the Shōgun carry imperial command, and that the Shōgun possesses the full confidence of the Court. To achieve this goal, the Shōgun must make himself vulnerable, and rely upon the Emperor to re-establish his authority.\n\nSuch a scheme is a fateful jump off the stage—if the Imperial Court is unwilling to cooperate, the Tokugawa will find themselves alone amidst their vengeful opponents."
imperial_restoration_kogi_yoron_loc: "For the crisis to end, the Emperor must rule. If the power of the Tokugawa is to survive restoration, the Shōgun must see it through on his own terms. The final step of the Shōgun's reforms must be to return administrative powers to the Emperor, and establish a new role for his clan within a reformed Imperial government.\n\nSuch a scheme is a fateful jump off the stage—if the Imperial Court is unwilling to cooperate, the Tokugawa will find themselves alone amidst their vengeful opponents."

je_meiji_restoration_imperial_marriage: "Arrange Imperial Marriage"
je_meiji_restoration_imperial_marriage_desc: "The project of #b Kōbu Gattai#! requires a union of the most literal sort—a political marriage between the sitting $RULER_TITLE_SHOGUN$ and an Imperial Princess. To realize this union, the $RULER_TITLE_SHOGUN$ must be prepared to meet the substantial conditions set forth by the Imperial Court."
je_meiji_restoration_imperial_marriage_conditions_tt: "To complete #v $je_meiji_imperial_marriage$#! [concept_journal_entry]:\n• $im_closed_borders_tt$\n• $im_free_trade_tt$\n• $im_treaty_port_tt$\n• If applicable: #indent_newline:3 \n• $im_broken_applicable_treaty_tt$"
im_treaty_port_tt: "No [concept_state] in [GetGeographicRegion('geographic_region_home_islands').GetName] is a [concept_treaty_port]"
